---
const pageTitle = 'About Me';

const identity = {
    firstName: 'Kristie',
    country: 'United Kingdom',
    occupation: 'UX Engineer',
    hobbies: ['web development','reading','design']
};

const skills = ['HTML', 'CSS', 'JavaScript', 'React', 'Figma', 'Markdown'];

const lucky = true;
const endOfTheWeek = false;
const goal = 4;
---

<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
		<link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
		<meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
		<title>{pageTitle}</title>
	</head>
	<body>
        <nav>
            <a href="/">Home</a>
            <a href="/about/">About</a>
            <a href="/blog/">Blog</a>
        </nav>
		<h1>{pageTitle}</h1>
        <h2>And my life so far...</h2>
        <p>Hello! My name is {identity.firstName}, a {identity.occupation} based in the {identity.country} with a passion for creating websites and continually learning new technologies.</p>
        <p>My interest in {identity.hobbies[0]} began when I was 24 years old, and it has grown into a genuine passion for building projects, solving problems, and exploring modern web technologies. One of the things I enjoy most about development is that there's always something new to learn, whether it's a new framework, programming technique, or {identity.hobbies[2]} approach, which is great! Because I also enjoy {identity.hobbies[1]}.</p>
        <p>Here is a few of my skills:</p>
        <ul>    
            {skills.map((skill) => <li>{skill}</li>)}
        </ul>
        {lucky && <p>I am very lucky to have had the life that I have had so far.</p>}
        {endOfTheWeek && <p>I finished setting up the blog!</p>}
        {goal === 4 ? <p>My goal is to finish the blog by the end of the week.</p> : <p>I did not finish the blog by the end of the week.</p>}
        <p>This blog is where I'll share my learning journey, projects, and experiences as I continue to develop my skills and explore the ever-evolving world of web development.</p>
    </body>
</html>
